## Process Management Commands

ps aux - Shows all running processes
top - Shows real-time process info
pgrep <name> - Search process by name
kill <PID> - Kill a process
systemctl status <service_name> - Shows status of a service
systemctl start <service_name> - To start a service
systemctl enable <service_name> - To enable a service

## File System Commands

ls - list files and directories
pwd - present working directory
cd - change directory
mkdir <direcory_name> - Create a directory
rm -r <directory_name> - To remove a directory and all its contents
cp <source_file> <location> - To copy a file from one directory to another
mv <old_name> <new_name> - To move/rename a file
cat <file_name> - To read a file
touch <file_name> - To create a file

## Network Troubleshooting

ping <destination> - To ping a destination
nslookup <destination> - To find IP address or domain name
traceroute <destination> - To determine the path taken and hops
netstat - To find information about network interface, Ip address etc.
ifconfig - Display or configure interfaces
route - to display the routing table
